fields.name: spikes.clusters
fields.description: [nspi]. Cluster assignments for each spike (integers counting from 0).

fields.name: spikes.times
fields.description: [nspi]. Times of spikes (seconds, relative to experiment onset). Note this includes spikes from all probes, merged together

fields.name: spikes.samples
fields.description: [nspi]. Sample index of spikes in their own electrophysiology binary file.

fields.name: clusters.uuids
fields.description: Unique identifier assigned to each cluster when ALF files created and during manual curation.

fields.name: clusters.amps
fields.description: Mean amplitude of each cluster (V)

fields.name: sparseNoise.xyPos
fields.description: 2 column array giving x and y coordiates on screen of sparse noise stimulus squares (WHAT UNIT?)

fields.name: _spikeglx_sync.channels
fields.description: 0 based index corresponding to the raw file sync channel used [0-15 on 3A, 0-8 on 3B]

fields.name: _spikeglx_sync.times
fields.description: [nsync]Times of sync pulses, seconds relative to ephys start

fields.name: spikes.amps
fields.description: [nspi]. Amplitude of each spike (V)

fields.name: clusters.metrics
fields.description: Quality control metrics at the cluster level. Fields may vary.

fields.name: clusters.waveformsChannels
fields.description: Index of channels that are stored for each cluster waveform. Sorted by increasing distance from the maximum amplitude channel.

fields.name: clusters.waveforms
fields.description: Waveform from spike sorting templates (stored as a sparse array, only for a subset of channels closest to the peak channel)

fields.name: clusters.peakToTrough
fields.description: Waveforms length in ms

fields.name: trials.probabilityLeft
fields.description: Probability that the stimulus will be on the left hand side for the current block. The probability of right is 1 minus this

fields.name: channels.rawInd
fields.description: [nch] Each channel's row in its home file (look up via probes.rawFileName), counting from zero. Note some rows don't have a channel, for example if they were sync pulses

fields.name: _spikeglx_sync.polarities
fields.description: [nsync]. Polarity of front: 1: rising, -1 falling

fields.name: clusters.depths
fields.description: [nc] Depth of mean cluster waveform on probe (µm). 0 means deepest site, positive means above this.

fields.name: spikes.depths
fields.description: [nspi]. Depth along probe of each spike (µm; computed from waveform center of mass). 0 means deepest site, positive means above this

fields.name: clusters.channels
fields.description: Channel which has the largest amplitude for this cluster. Note this counts all channels in the whole recording (starting from zero), rather than just the channels on this cluster's home probe - so if you want to find this cluster's brain location, it would be channels.brainLocation[clusters.peakChannel[i],:]

fields.name: camera.dlc
fields.description: Raw DLC output for Camera as numpy array

fields.name: ephysData.raw.ap
fields.description: Action Potentials band of raw neurophysiology data - mtscomp compressed

fields.name: ephysData.raw.lf
fields.description: Low Field band of raw neurophysiology data - mtscomp compressed

fields.name: ephysData.raw.nidq
fields.description: Nidq breakout box binary data for Neuropixel 3B system - mtscomp compressed

fields.name: ephysData.raw.ch
fields.description: mtscomp header file for block compressed binary time-series.

fields.name: ephysData.raw.meta
fields.description: Metadata text file for raw binary neurophysiology data

fields.name: ephysData.raw.sync
fields.description: Synchronization file for multi-probes acquisitions.

fields.name: ephysData.raw.timestamps
fields.description: 2 columns file containing time synchronisation information for the AP binary file: sample index in the first column and session time in the second column. Note that sample indices may not be integers.

fields.name: ephysData.raw.wiring
fields.description: Description of wiring of synchronization auxiliaries

fields.name: channels.probes
fields.description: Probe assignments for each channel (integers counting from 0). Can be used as direct indexing for the probes.* attributes.

fields.name: clusters.probes
fields.description: Probe assignments for each cluster (integers counting from 0). Can be used as direct indexing for the probes.* attributes.

fields.name: spikes.templates
fields.description: Detection template assignment for each spike (integers counting from 0). Can be used as direct indexing of the templates.* attributes.

fields.name: channels.localCoordinates
fields.description: relative to probe coordinate system (µm): x (first) dimension is on the width of the shank while (y) is the depth where 0 is the deepest site, and positive above this.

fields.name: camera.times
fields.description: Synchronized time stamps for camera

fields.name: templates.waveformsChannels
fields.description: Index of channels that are stored for each template. Sorted by increasing distance from the maximum amplitude channel.

fields.name: templates.waveforms
fields.description: Waveform of automatic spike sorting templates (stored as a sparse array, only for a subset of channels closest to the peak channel)

fields.name: templates.amps
fields.description: Average peak/trough amplitude of templates

fields.name: probes.description
fields.description: JSON with one entry per probe containing label, model (3A, 3B1, 3B2),serial and raw_file_name

fields.name: probes.trajectory
fields.description:
JSON with one entry per probe containing the 7 parameters describing the probe trajectory. Refer to the coordinate section of this document for more information.
 'x':(um) medio-lateral coordinate relative to Bregma, left negative
 'y':(um) antero-posterior coordinate relative to Bregma, back negative
 'z':(um) dorso-ventral coordinate relative to Bregma, ventral negative
 'phi':(degrees)[-180 180] azimuth
 'theta':(degrees)[0 180] polar angle
 'depth':(um) insertion depth
 'beta' :(degrees) roll angle of the probe"

fields.name: kilosort.whitening_matrix
fields.description: Whitening matrix applied by kilosort2, [nchannels, nchannels]

fields.name: _phy_spikes_subset.channels
fields.description: Channel index for sample waveforms, [nspikes, nchannelsmax]

fields.name: _phy_spikes_subset.spikes
fields.description: Spikes index for sample waveforms, [nspikes,]

fields.name: _phy_spikes_subset.waveforms
fields.description: Sample waveforms, [nspikes, nsamples, nchannelsmax]

fields.name: clusters.brainLocationIds_ccf_2017
fields.description: Brain location id of clusters following ephys alignment obtained from 25um resolution 2017 Allen Common Coordinate Framework

fields.name: clusters.brainLocationAcronyms_ccf_2017
fields.description: Brain location acronym of clusters following ephys alignment obtained from 25um resolution 2017 Allen Common Coordinate Framework

fields.name: clusters.mlapdv
fields.description: 3d location of the cluster relative to bregma following ephys alignment - mediolateral; anterior-posterior; dorsoventral coordinates (um)

fields.name: channels.brainLocationIds_ccf_2017
fields.description: Brain location id of channels following ephys alignment obtained from 25um resolution 2017 Allen Common Coordinate Framework

fields.name: channels.mlapdv
fields.description: 3d location of the channels relative to bregma following ephys alignment - mediolateral; anterior-posterior; dorsoventral coordinates (um)

fields.name: _kilosort_raw.output
fields.description: Spike sorting output from kilosort

fields.name: drift.um
fields.description: Result of the drift registration. 1D vector of drift estimation in um. A cell moving downwards relative to the probe will show as negative drift (ie. it overlays on the raster). For non-rigid drift, 2D vector where the first dimension corresponds to the time of the estimation and the second dimension to the depth of the estimate (see the scale datasets)

fields.name: drift_depths.um
fields.description: For non-rigid registration, depth corresponding to each of the drift matrix column (um)

fields.name: drift.times
fields.description: Time of the probe corresponding to each of the drift matrix row (secs)

fields.name: licks.times
fields.description: Times of licks as detected from DLC tongue traces.

fields.name: electrodeSites.localCoordinates
fields.description: Location of each channel relative to probe coordinate system (µm): (first) dimension is on the width of the shank; Second is the depth where 0 is the deepest site, and positive above this. Straight mapping to the raw electrophysiology binary files

fields.name: electrodeSites.mlapdv
fields.description: 3d location of the channels relative to bregma following ephys alignment - mediolateral; anterior-posterior; dorsoventral coordinates (um) straight mapping to the raw electrophysiology binary file channels

fields.name: electrodeSites.brainLocationIds_ccf_2017
fields.description: Brain location id of channels following ephys alignment obtained from 25um resolution 2017 Allen Common Coordinate Framework - straight mapping to the raw electrophysiology binary file channels.

fields.name: widefieldU.images
fields.description: Projected SVD spatial components (denoised/decomposed) with the shape [H, W, nComponents] where H and W are the dimensions of a single frame.

fields.name: widefieldSVT.uncorrected
fields.description: temporal SVD components (denoised/decomposed), s·Vᵀ with dimensions [nComponents, nFrames]

fields.name: widefieldSVT.haemoCorrected
fields.description: hemodynamic corrected temporal SVD components with dimensions [nComponents, nFrames]

fields.name: widefield.times
fields.description: the time of each frame in seconds from experiment start

fields.name: widefield.raw.meta
fields.description: information about the dataset such as frame rate and number of channels

fields.name: widefieldLandmarks.dorsalCortex
fields.description: Manually identified dorsal cortex landmark coordinates for alignment

fields.name: widefieldEvents.raw
fields.description: Widefield frame information and IO states; 2 columns are (frame#, timestamp)

fields.name: widefield.raw
fields.description: Compressed raw video data with dimensions [nFrames, H, W]

fields.name: widefieldChannels.frameAverage
fields.description: average across all frames for each channel of imaging

fields.name: widefieldChannels.wiring
fields.description: For each LED channel there is an indentifier (typically an int channel number) and a corresponding wavelength.

fields.name: photometry.signal
fields.description: the recorded signal for each frame.

fields.name: photometry.ROIs
fields.description: ROI integer for associating with trajectory.

fields.name: photometryFibers.brainLocationAcronyms_ccf_2017
fields.description: Extracted brainlocation after histology per ROI.

fields.name: imaging.frames
fields.description: Raw frame images with the dimensions [nframes, nx, ny(, nchannels)]. Note that depending on modality, multiple planes and channels may be stitched together and/or presented in a different order.

fields.name: imaging.times
fields.description: The times of frame acquisition.

fields.name: imaging.imagingLightSource
fields.description: int representing which channel was acquired for each frame. 0 channel indicates no light.

fields.name: imagingLightSource.properties
fields.description: A map of channels number, colour and wavelength.  NB: This is the light source wavelength, not the photosensor channel / emitted wavelength.

fields.name: DAQdata.raw
fields.description: The output of the DAQ software for a given device.  The namespace should identify the DAQ model or acquisition software, e.g. 'mcc', 'ni' or 'timeline'.

fields.name: DAQdata.timestamps
fields.description: The DAQ software timestamps for a given device.  The namespace should identify the DAQ model or acquisition software, e.g. 'mcc', 'ni' or 'timeline'.

fields.name: DAQdata.meta
fields.description: Associated DAQ metadata, such as input and output channel configurations. The metadata structure varies between namespaces.

fields.name: DAQdata.wiring
fields.description: A map of the channel IDs and their corresponding device label, e.g. {ai1: bpod}.

fields.name: mpci.componentsActivity
fields.description: SVT of singular value compression, separately for each plane

fields.name: mpci.ROIActivityF
fields.description: Mean activity of all pixels in each ROI

fields.name: mpci.ROINeuropilActivityF
fields.description: Mean activity neuropil pixels neighboring each ROI

fields.name: mpci.ROIActivityDeconvolved
fields.description: Neuropil-subtracted deconvolved activity of each ROI using standard parameters

fields.name: mpci.times
fields.description: Times of each frame

fields.name: mpci.badFrames
fields.description: Bad frames as identified by processing software

fields.name: mpci.mpciFrameQC
fields.description: Frame-level quality control as added by experimenter. 0 means good, other values defined in mpciFrameQC.names.tsv

fields.name: mpciFrameQC.names
fields.description: Human-readable definition of QC types. First column, 'qc_values', contains unsigned ints where 0 always should mean good. Second column, 'qc_labels', contains a short human-readable description.

fields.name: mpciComponents.images
fields.description: Component image for each plane

fields.name: mpciMeanImage.images
fields.description: Mean image for each plane and each channel. Channel 0 should be the calcium-sensitive channel

fields.name: mpciROIs.stackPos
fields.description: X, Y, and Z (plane) pixel coordinates of each ROI's centroid.

fields.name: mpciROIs.mlapdv
fields.description: 3D location of the ROI centroid relative to bregma - mediolateral; anterior-posterior; dorsoventral coordinates (um). '_estimate' means not resolved with histology.

fields.name: mpciROIs.mpciROITypes
fields.description: Numerical enumeration of ROI type for each ROI.

fields.name: mpciROIs.masks
fields.description: Floating-point mask of each ROI, in 2D or 3D according to how you did detection. Saved as a sparse array. sum(roi_mask * frames[ypix, xpix, :]) = fluorescence

fields.name: mpciROIs.neuropilMasks
fields.description: Boolean neuropil mask for each ROI, in 2D or 3D according to how you did detection. Saved as a sparse array.

fields.name: mpciROITypes.names
fields.description: Human-readable definition of ROI types (neuron, dendrite, etc). First column, 'roi_values', contains the ROI type enumeration.  The second, 'roi_labels', contains a string description.

fields.name: mpciROIs.cellClassifier
fields.description: Floating-point cell classifier score for each ROI, ranging between 0 and 1

fields.name: mpciStack.timeshift
fields.description: Offset time for scanning of each voxel in the stack

fields.name: referenceImage.raw
fields.description: A fullfield multiphoton imaging picture for use in histology alignment.

fields.name: ROIData.raw
fields.description: Raw cell detection output ROI data.

fields.name: mpciROIs.brainLocationIds
fields.description: Brain location acronym of each ROI centroid. A '_ccf_2017' in the dataset means an alignment obtained from 25um resolution 2017 Allen Common Coordinate Framework. '_estimate' means not resolved with histology.

fields.name: widefieldU.mask
fields.description: Mask to apply to widefield session data prior to pre-processing steps

fields.name: mpciMeanImage.brainLocationIds
fields.description: Brain location acronym of each pixel of the mean image. A '_ccf_2017' in the dataset means an alignment obtained from 25um resolution 2017 Allen Common Coordinate Framework. '_estimate' means not resolved with histology.

fields.name: mpciMeanImage.mlapdv
fields.description: 3D location of the cluster relative to bregma of each pixel of the mean image - mediolateral; anterior-posterior; dorsoventral coordinates (um). '_estimate' means not resolved with histology.

fields.name: subjectWidefieldU.mask_atlasTransformed
fields.description: Mask to apply to all widefield sessions from a subject after pre-processing and atlas alignment

fields.name: referenceImage.stack
fields.description: A stitched mean multiphoton imaging stack, containing X and Y resolution/size information in the tiff header.  Used in histology alignment.

fields.name: referenceImage.meta
fields.description: Stack image meta-data listing the depth in microns of each slice in the stack, and ML and AP coordinates of the center.

fields.name: mpciROIs.uuids
fields.description: Unique identifier assigned to each ROI when ALF files created after ROI detection.

fields.name: photometryROI.locations
fields.description: Look up table from photometry ROI, to fiber name registered in the database and Allen brain location

fields.name: waveforms.traces
fields.description: Snippets of lightly preprocessed waveforms from spikes, organized by unit.

fields.name: waveforms.templates
fields.description: Medians of unit waveforms.

fields.name: waveforms.table
fields.description: Table containing the sample index, cluster id, and peak channel id for each waveform extracted.

fields.name: waveforms.channels
fields.description: Array containing the channel ids for each waveform.

fields.name: channels.labels
fields.description: Bad channel detection outcome, 0 is good, 1 corresponds to dead or low amplitude channels, 2 corresponds to noisy channels, 3 corresponds to channels labeled as outside of the brain.

fields.name: rawImagingData.times
fields.description: The raw frame exposure times.

fields.name: clusters.curatedLabels
fields.description: Manually annotated cluster labels

fields.name: iblsorter_parameters
fields.description: Spike sorting parameters
